abstract: Cuba releases more than two dozen dissidents, some of them believed to be among 53 it had agreed to free as the United States and Cuba decided to normalize diplomatic relations.
lead_paragraph: Some of the prisoners were believed to be among 53 that Cuba had agreed to free last month as part of a thaw with the United States.

headline.main: Cuba Is Reported to Release 26 Dissidents
